<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pocean.2019.102222" author="Gebruk, AV" journalOrPublisher="Part I, Oceanographic Research Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B30" refString="Gebruk, AV, Kremenetskaia, A, Rouse, GW, 2020. A group of species &quot;Psychropotes longicauda&quot; (Psychropotidae, Elasipodida, Holothuroidea) from the Kuril-Kamchatka Trench area (North-West Pacific). Progress in Oceanography 180: e102222. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pocean.2019.102222" title="A group of species &quot; Psychropotes longicauda &quot; (Psychropotidae, Elasipodida, Holothuroidea) from the Kuril-Kamchatka Trench area (North-West Pacific). Progress in Oceanography 180: e 102222." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pocean.2019.102222" year="2020">Gebruk et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
morphologically examined the specimen collected during the DeepCCZ and re-established the species 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Clark" baseAuthorityYear="1920" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae " genus="Psychropotes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Psychropotes dyscrita" order="Elasipodida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="dyscrita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Psychropotes dyscrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on this specimen. The holotype was collected in Peru, at 5206 m depth, and the species is known from the Central Pacific Ocean at depths of 5040-5206 m (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pocean.2019.102222" author="Gebruk, AV" journalOrPublisher="Part I, Oceanographic Research Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B30" refString="Gebruk, AV, Kremenetskaia, A, Rouse, GW, 2020. A group of species &quot;Psychropotes longicauda&quot; (Psychropotidae, Elasipodida, Holothuroidea) from the Kuril-Kamchatka Trench area (North-West Pacific). Progress in Oceanography 180: e102222. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pocean.2019.102222" title="A group of species &quot; Psychropotes longicauda &quot; (Psychropotidae, Elasipodida, Holothuroidea) from the Kuril-Kamchatka Trench area (North-West Pacific). Progress in Oceanography 180: e 102222." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pocean.2019.102222" year="2020">Gebruk et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Clark" baseAuthorityYear="1920" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae " genus="Psychropotes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Psychropotes dyscrita" order="Elasipodida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="dyscrita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Psychropotes dyscrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. moskalevi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="moskalevi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. moskalevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gebruk &amp; Kremenetskaia, 2020 are the two only known yellow species for this genus and were recovered as sister species (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="F34" captionText="Figure 34. Phylogenetic tree of the class Holothuroidea. Concatenated (12 S, 16 S, 18 S, 28 S, COI, and H 3) median consensus BEAST tree with posterior probability (PP) and bootstrap (BS) values indicated. Only values of PP&gt; 0.70 and BS&gt; 50 are shown, with values of PP&gt; 0.95 and BS&gt; 90 indicated with a circle. Nodes not recovered on the RAxML tree are indicated with a hyphen. Sequences generated in this study are highlighted in violet." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716360" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">34</figureCitation>
). The COI sequence for the DeepCCZ specimen is 1.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.4% divergent (K2P distance) from specimens of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. moskalevi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="moskalevi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. moskalevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although this value seems low, the COI gene seems to be more conserved in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theel" authorityYear="1882" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae " genus="Psychropotes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Psychropotes" order="Elasipodida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Psychropotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(1.1-13.4%, mean = 6.5%), with &lt;2% interspecific divergence between some species pairs (
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. dyscrita" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dyscrita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. dyscrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. moskalevi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="moskalevi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. moskalevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. moskalevi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="moskalevi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. moskalevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. raripes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="raripes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. raripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ludwig, 1893).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The specimen was found on the sediment seafloor of an abyssal plain in APEI 4 at 5040 m depth.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="comparisons">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Comparison with image-based catalogue.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A very similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theel" authorityYear="1882" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae " genus="Psychropotes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Psychropotes" order="Elasipodida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Psychropotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. morphotype (i.e., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theel" authorityYear="1882" class="Holothuroidea" family="Psychropotidae " genus="Psychropotes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Psychropotes" order="Elasipodida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Psychropotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. indet., HOL_047) has been encountered in seabed image surveys conducted across nodule fields areas of the eastern CCZ (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Tilot, V" journalOrPublisher="Zoology (Jena, Germany)" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B97" refString="Tilot, V, 2006. Biodiversity and Distribution of the Megafauna. In: Commission IO (Ed.) Technical Series 69. Project Unesco COI/Min, Vlanderen." title="Biodiversity and Distribution of the Megafauna. In: Commission IO (Ed.) Technical Series 69. Project Unesco COI / Min, Vlanderen." year="2006">Tilot 2006</bibRefCitation>
), and in the Kiribati EEZ, where this taxon was the most abundant holothurian encountered (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3389/fmars.2019.00605" author="Simon-Lledo, E" journalOrPublisher="Limnology and Oceanography" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B87" refString="Simon-Lledo, E, Thompson, S, Yool, A, Flynn, A, Pomee, C, Parianos, J, Jones, DOB, 2019d. Preliminary Observations of the Abyssal Megafauna of Kiribati. Frontiers in Marine Science 605: e605. https://doi.org/10.3389/fmars.2019.00605" title="Preliminary Observations of the Abyssal Megafauna of Kiribati. Frontiers in Marine Science 605: e 605." url="https://doi.org/10.3389/fmars.2019.00605" year="2019 d">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Simon-Lledó">Simon-Lledo</normalizedToken>
et al. 2019d
</bibRefCitation>
). In pioneer seabed image surveys conducted at the CCZ, prior to the re-establishment of the species (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pocean.2019.102222" author="Gebruk, AV" journalOrPublisher="Part I, Oceanographic Research Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B30" refString="Gebruk, AV, Kremenetskaia, A, Rouse, GW, 2020. A group of species &quot;Psychropotes longicauda&quot; (Psychropotidae, Elasipodida, Holothuroidea) from the Kuril-Kamchatka Trench area (North-West Pacific). Progress in Oceanography 180: e102222. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pocean.2019.102222" title="A group of species &quot; Psychropotes longicauda &quot; (Psychropotidae, Elasipodida, Holothuroidea) from the Kuril-Kamchatka Trench area (North-West Pacific). Progress in Oceanography 180: e 102222." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pocean.2019.102222" year="2020">Gebruk et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
), this morphotype was typically classified as 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. longicauda" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="longicauda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. longicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.Based on seabed imagery (e.g., without analysis of ossicles), it is not possible to determine whether HOL_047 specimens are 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. dyscrita" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dyscrita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. dyscrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. moskalevi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="moskalevi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. moskalevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
